    • Method Detail

      • newByteArray

        public byte[] newByteArray(int arrayLength)
                    throws InterruptedException
        Allocate a byte array, where the length of the allocated array is the least power of two of the given length unless the given length is less than ByteArrayManager.MIN_ARRAY_LENGTH. In such case, the returned array length is equal to ByteArrayManager.MIN_ARRAY_LENGTH. If the number of allocated arrays exceeds the capacity, the current thread is blocked until the number of allocated arrays drops to below the capacity. The byte array allocated by this method must be returned for recycling via the release(byte[]) method.
        Specified by:
        newByteArray in class ByteArrayManager
        Returns:
        a byte array with length larger than or equal to the given length.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException

      • release

        public int release(byte[] array)
        Recycle the given byte array. The byte array may or may not be allocated by the newByteArray(int) method. This is a non-blocking call.
        Specified by:
        release in class ByteArrayManager
        Returns:
        the number of free array.
